        correct: 2,
        rationale: "Positive Nikolsky sign (epidermal detachment with lateral pressure) and mucosal involvement (oral, conjunctival, or genital erosions) are hallmark findings of SJS/TEN that distinguish it from benign morbilliform eruption. Skin pain disproportionate to appearance is an early warning sign. A simple morbilliform eruption does not cause epidermal detachment or mucosal involvement."
