    pearls: ["The Gell-Coombs classification has 4 types: Type I (immediate/IgE), Type II (cytotoxic/IgG-IgM), Type III (immune complex), Type IV (delayed/T-cell) — Types I-III are antibody-mediated; Type IV is cell-mediated","Penicillin allergy is the most commonly reported drug allergy (~10% of patients), but >90% of patients labeled 'penicillin allergic' can tolerate penicillin when formally tested — penicillin allergy delabeling is a critical antimicrobial stewardship initiative","The 10% penicillin-cephalosporin cross-reactivity rate is a MYTH based on flawed 1960s-70s data — actual cross-reactivity is 1-2% and is based on R1 side-chain similarity, not the beta-lactam ring","DRESS syndrome has a paradoxically LONG latency (2-8 weeks) compared to other drug reactions — the delayed onset often leads to failure to recognize the drug as causative; liver involvement (hepatitis) occurs in ~80% and drives mortality","SJS/TEN SCORTEN scoring predicts mortality: age >40, malignancy, tachycardia >120, BSA >10%, BUN >28, glucose >252, bicarb <20 — each point increases mortality; score ≥5 = >90% mortality"],
